</div> 
<p><strong>Moonveil</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Katanas" href="/Katanas" target="">Katana</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Moonveil</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence" target="">Intelligence</a>&nbsp;and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for dealing melee <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Slash Damage" href="/Slash+Damage">Slash</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Pierce Damage" href="/Pierce+Damage">Pierce</a> Damage in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Combat" href="/Combat">Combat</a>. Its accompanying unique skill can also allow the user to draw the weapon at great speed for an instant slash attack and fires off a wave of light.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Katana forged of glintstone.<br>Masterpiece of a Sellian swordsmith.&nbsp;</em></p> 
 <p><em>Light&nbsp;enwreathes the blade when sheathed, explaining its Moonveil moniker.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Moonveil in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Moonveil weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Obtained upon defeating the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magma Wyrm" href="/Magma+Wyrm" target="">Magma Wyrm</a>&nbsp;located&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Gael Tunnel" href="/Gael+Tunnel" target="">Gael Tunnel</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Caelid" href="/Caelid" target="">Caelid</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=2909&amp;lat=-174.156251&amp;lng=126.82006&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=2909&amp;lat=-174.156251&amp;lng=126.82006&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Map Link</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Moonveil Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>:&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Transient Moonlight" href="/Transient+Moonlight" target="">Transient Moonlight</a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Sheathe blade, holding it at the hip in a composed stance. Follow up with either a normal or a strong attack to draw the blade at great speed for an instant slash attack. Both attacks fire off a wave of light, matching&nbsp;the orientation of the blade,&nbsp;with normal attacks firing a horizontal&nbsp;&amp; short-range wave, and strong attacks firing a vertical &amp; long-range wave that travels along the ground. The&nbsp;wave of light and melee swipe deal damage independently,&nbsp;allowing enemies to be hit by both for increased damage when in melee range.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>This weapon can't be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li>Can't be enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;nor boosted by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a></li> 
 <li>Can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Causes&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Hemorrhage" href="/Hemorrhage">Blood loss</a>&nbsp;Buildup:&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Hemorrhage" href="/Hemorrhage"><img title="Causes Blood Loss Buildup" src="/file/Elden-Ring/hemmorage.png" alt="hemmorage" width="18">&nbsp;(50)</a></li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
