				<li id="16768170" class="cmnt-root" data="1" data-d="1662351408000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=110969" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">Sujiren99</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578660/Moonveil" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">05 Sep 2022 00:16</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16768170" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I&apos;ll be honest. IDK how good Moonveil is in PVE, but  currently this weapon is literally broken in pvp and just about every mage and their moms use it. The mages that don&apos;t use it are infinitely easier to beat, at least from my dueling experience, I&apos;m just saying the truth.<br/><br/>What makes Moonveil broken you might ask? Because the weapon art is literally Unsheathe ( Which is already a very good AOW btw), except with basically 5 times the range and practically the same damage.<br/><br/>In before someone downvotes my comment saying &quot;Hurr Durr Moonveil is easy to dodge&quot; Well no ****, everything is easy to dodge if your actively looking out for it.<br/><br/>The thing is Moonveil&apos;s AOW is so fast and has so much range, that it&apos;s literally &quot;punish everything button&quot; Opponent whiffed an attack? Moonveil. Opponent is trying to cast a spell? Moonveil. Opponent is trying to drink a mana pot? Moonveil. Opponent wants to trade? Moonveil.<br/><br/>Essentially the weapon art forces you to play extremely passively, unless you want to get two shotted by it. You know what happens when you play passively vs a mage? You get spammed by sorceries. Pair it with the fact that most mages that use Moonveil are the same sweats that also wear full or almost full Veterans set, and it becomes nearly impossible to outrade them.<br/><br/>Basically for a single weapon, Moonveil puts far too much pressure on your opponent. I imagine it&apos;s gonna get ROB treatment in a couple of patches.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16768170" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16768170" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>5</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>4</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16768170"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16768170" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16768170"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
